## S 5. Reply/Comment Flow (after compose dialog is open)

Use for replies, comments, quotes, and original posts (AFTER dialog is open).

**Submit button differs by context:**
- Reply/Comment: `button[aria-label="Publish reply"]`
- Quote post / Original post: `button[aria-label="Publish post"]`

The script below tries "Publish reply" first, falls back to "Publish post" — works for ALL cases.

**ONE evaluate** — wait 1.5s + type + wait 0.5s + click submit:

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500));
    const dialog = document.querySelector('[role="dialog"]');
    if (!dialog) return { error: 'no_dialog' };
    const textbox = dialog.querySelector('[role="textbox"][contenteditable="true"]');
    if (!textbox) return { error: 'no_textbox' };
    textbox.focus();
    document.execCommand('insertText', false, '${commentText.replace(/'/g, "\\'")}');
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
    const submitBtn = dialog.querySelector('button[aria-label="Publish reply"]')
                   || dialog.querySelector('button[aria-label="Publish post"]');
    if (!submitBtn) return { typed: true, error: 'no_submit_button' };
    submitBtn.click();
    return { typed: true, submitted: true };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

**Replies-disabled posts:** If "Compose reply" button is missing on a post page (author restricted replies), skip to next candidate. Do NOT error — just log and move on.

Do NOT verify after submit — replies/comments work reliably. Dialog closes on success.
